The father of late Orlando Pirates and Bafana Bafana goalkeeper Senzo Meyiwa has died.  It was reported that Sam was in and out of hospital and was rushed to the Prince Mshiyeni Memorial Hospital in Umlazi, south of Durban, after suffering a stroke last year August. Earlier this year, his family told Daily Sun that his health is failing because his son, late Orlando Pirates goalkeeper Senzo’s murder case, hasn’t been solved. According to Sfiso Meyiwa his son Mr Sam Meyiwa, never recovered fully when he had a stroke and he had the second one and was hospitalized again last month and eventually passed on from home early this morning     